ays in which contemporary artists across different media and diverse cultural contexts – including the UK, Europe, the USA and Latin America – continue to engage with Beckett. The book offers fresh insights into how his work has kept inspiring both practitioners and audiences in the twenty-first century, operating through methodologies and approaches that aim to facilitate and establish the study of modern-day adaptations, not just of Beckett but other (multimedia) authors as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  aSamuel Beckett.  aadaptation.  aappropriation.  ainstallation.  aintermediality.  aintertextuality.  amultimediality.  aperformance.  aremediation.  atransmediality.1 aBeloborodova, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBignell, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBignell, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBird, Dúnlaith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCardona, Luz María Sánchez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClavier, Evelyne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGontarski, S. E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerren, Graley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, David Houston, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMullan, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMullan, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcTighe, Trish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, Paul